The Committee of Ministers of the Council of Europe will consider the possibility of Russia's expulsion from the Council of Europe at its second consecutive extraordinary meeting tomorrow.
This is stated in the decision of the extraordinary meeting of the Committee of Ministers of the Council of Europe regarding Russia's military attack on Ukraine, which was attended by representatives of 47 member states of the Council of Europe, the press service of the Council of Europe reported to Ukrinform.
In particular, in the decision adopted yesterday, the Committee of Ministers:
strongly condemned the armed attack of the Russian Federation on Ukraine in violation of international law;
decided without delay and in close coordination with the Parliamentary Assembly and the Secretary General to consider the measures to be taken in response to the serious breach by the Russian Federation of its statutory obligations as a member state of the Council of Europe;
called on the Russian Federation to immediately and unconditionally stop its military actions in Ukraine;
condemned the recognition by the Russian Federation of the Ukrainian regions of Donetsk and Luhansk as independent entities;
confirmed his steadfast commitment to the independence, sovereignty and territorial integrity of Ukraine within its internationally recognized borders;
expressed his support for Ukraine and solidarity with its people.
"The Committee of Ministers also agreed to hold another extraordinary meeting on February 25, 2022, in order to consider the measures that must be taken, including in accordance with Article 8 of the Statute of the Council of Europe," the message reads.
The mentioned Article of the Statute (Article 8), in particular provides: "Any member of the Council of Europe who has grossly violated Article 3 may be temporarily deprived of the right of representation, and the Committee of Ministers may ask him to leave the Council in accordance with Article 7. If such a member of the Council does not comply with this request, the Committee may decide to terminate his membership of the Council, starting from a date that the Committee may determine."
As reported by Ukrinform, on February 24, the head of the aggressor country, Vladimir Putin, announced the beginning of the invasion of the territory of Ukraine. Around 4 a.m., Russia started a war and struck Ukrainian cities.
The President of Ukraine, Volodymyr Zelenskyy, declared that martial law is being introduced throughout the territory of Ukraine. On the morning of February 24, the Verkhovna Rada approved Zelenskyi's decree on the introduction of martial law throughout Ukraine.
